<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ITEM 1.&nbsp;&nbsp;BUSINES
</FONT>
<A NAME="KLX-20160131X10K_HTM_ITEM1BUSINESS_810390">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	S
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Except as otherwise indicated or unless the context otherwise requires,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	KLX,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	we,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	us
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	refer to KLX&nbsp;Inc. and its consolidated subsidiaries after giving effect to the internal reorganization and its spin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;off from B/E Aerospace, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	B/E Aerospace
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	refers to B/E Aerospace,&nbsp;Inc., its predecessors and its consolidated subsidiaries, other than, for all periods following the spin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;off, KLX&nbsp;Inc. and its consolidated subsidiaries. See
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Item&nbsp;7. Management
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x2014;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Overview
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x2014;The Spin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	off.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Our Company
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe, based on our experience in the industry, that we are the world
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s leading distributor and value
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;added service provider of aerospace fasteners and consumables, and that we offer one of the broadest ranges of aerospace hardware and consumables and inventory management services worldwide. Through organic growth and a number of strategic acquisitions beginning in 2001, we believe we have become our industry
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s leading provider of aerospace fasteners, consumable products and supply chain management services. Through our global facilities network and advanced information technology systems, we offer unparalleled service to commercial airline, business jet and defense original equipment manufacturers and their subcontractors (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	OEMs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	airlines,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	maintenance, repair and overhaul (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	MRO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	) operators, and fixed base operators (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	FBOs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	). With a large and diverse global customer base, including virtually all of the world
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s commercial
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	airline
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, business jet and defense OEMs, OEM subcontractors
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, airlines
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and major MRO operators across five continents, w
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	e provide access to over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	one million stock keeping units (&#x201C;SKUs&#x201D;). We serve as a distributor for every major aerospace fastener manufacturer. In order to support our vast range of custom products and servic
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	es, we have invested over $100
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million in proprietary information technology (&#x201C;IT&#x201D;) systems to create a superior technology platform. Our systems support both internal distribution processes and part attributes, along with customer services, including just
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;time (&#x201C;JIT&#x201D;) deliveries and kitting solutions, which we believe are unmatched by any competitor. This business is operated within our Aerospace Solutions Group (&#x201C;ASG&#x201D;) segment.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	During
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ended January 31, 2016 (&#x201C;Fiscal 2015&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ASG generated approximately 85
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% of our consolidated revenues.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our ASG segment has maintained strong, collaborative, long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;standing relationships with its customers. As a result of our operational and information technology systems, we have historically been able to ship approximately 60% of our orders within 24&nbsp;hours of receipt of the order. Our seasoned purchasing and sales teams, coupled with state
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;art IT and automated parts retrieval systems, help us to sustain our reputation for highly dependable, rapid, on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;time delivery.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ASG sells fasteners and other consumable products to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6,000 customers throughout the wo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	rld. Its top five customers in Fiscal 2015
</FONT>

	collectively accounted for approximately 3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% of ASG&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	revenues.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In the latter part of 2013, we initiated an expansion into the energy services sector. Since then, we have acquired seven companies dedicated to providing technical services and related rental equipment to oil and gas exploration and production companies. As a result, we now provide a broad range of solutions and equipment which bring value
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;added resources to a new customer base, often in remote locations on an episodic or urgent 24/7 basis. Our customers include independent and major oil and gas companies that are engaged in the exploration and production (&#x201C;E&amp;P&#x201D;) of oil and gas properties in onshore North America, including in the Northeast (Marcellus and Utica Shale), Rocky Mountains (Williston and Piceance Basins), Southwest (Permian Basin and Eagle Ford) and Mid
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Continent. This business is operated within our Energy Services Group (&#x201C;ESG&#x201D;) segment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	ESG

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Industry Overview
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Aerospace Solutions Group
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ASG
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is generally segmented by end customer or sales channel. Based on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our experience in this industry
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, we estimate that during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the market for the products and services provided by ASG, other than chemicals, adhesives and other related products, was approximately $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;billion; of this amount, we estimate that approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	34
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	%, or $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1.6

	&nbsp;billion, is served by the manufacturers of these products directly to the en
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	d customers and approximately 66

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	%, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$3.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;billion, is served by stocking distributors such as ASG.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe that there is a direct relationship between demand for fasteners and other consumable products and airliner fleet size, aircraft utilization and aircraft age, as well as new aircraft production rates. All aircraft must be serviced at regular intervals, which drives aftermarket demand for aerospace fasteners and consumable product
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s. ASG generated approximately 36
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% of its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	revenues from aftermarket sales to support the in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;service fleet of commercial aircraft, business jet manufacturers and the global fleet of military aircraft. Historically, aerospace fastener and consumable products revenues have been derived from the following sources:
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Demand for structural aircraft modifications, cabin interior modifications and passenger
</FONT>

	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition, suppliers in the aerospace, defense and related industries increasingly rely on companies such as ASG to provide a customized single point of contact for inventory management, customized invoicing, automated forecasting and usage monitoring, centralized communications and tracking across their broad and varied supply base.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Since 2010, as the global economy began to recover from recession, increased passenger traffic volumes and the return to profitability of the global airline industry have created significant demand for c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ommercial aircraft. The Airline Monitor forecasts a 2016 global passenger tra
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ffic increase of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% and projects long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;term growth at an approximate compounded annual growth rate (&#x201C;CAGR&#x201D;) of 5.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% during the 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;2030 period. The International Air Transport Association (&#x201C;IATA&#x201D;) expects global airline profits to improve to $3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;billion in 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% higher than 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, marking the global airline industry&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	seventh
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	consecutive year of record profitability.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Many airlines deferred the replacement of a large number of aging aircraft over the 2000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;2009 period. This, combined with recent more efficient new aircraft introductions, the growing requirements for more aircraft to support projected long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;term traffic growth, record capacity utilization rates, high fuel costs and the low cost of financing new aircraft drove the global airline industry to place record orders for new airc
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	raft. Backlogs at Airbus&nbsp;S.A.S. (&#x201C;Airbus&#x201D;) and The Boeing Company (&#x201C;Boeing&#x201D;) stood at record levels of approximately 6,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	818
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and 5,813
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	aircraft
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, respectively, at January 31, 2016. They have reported that they each have an approximate eight
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to ten-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	year backlog. As a result, most industry analysts believe the outlook for new aircraft deliveries will be strong for the foreseeable future.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The strong new aircraft delivery cycle has resulted in an increase in ASG
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s revenues to support the global aerospace manufacturing base, including several new long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;term contract awards. However, unlike any prior new aircraft
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	delivery cycle, a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	record number of new aircraft deliveries were to replace and retire older, less fuel efficient aircraft. These retirements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, along with foreign currency headwinds,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	negatively impacted our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	aftermarket revenues and the higher margins related thereto. We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	anticipate a somewhat higher level of aftermarket activity over the next year to support
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	25,000 airliners in the commercial airline fleet, including the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	8,100
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	new aircraft delivered over the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	past six years as these aircraft
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	begin to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	roll off their warranty periods and begin to require periodic heavy maintenance checks.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage7"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#KLX-20160131X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Defense spending has historically been driven by the timing of military aircraft orders and evolving government strategies and policies. We also support military aircraft MRO providers. Defense spending began to decline in 2012 as the U.S. government implemented its sequestration program. As a result, we have seen demand from our military and defense customers decline from peak levels experienced prior to 2012.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	material improvement in the military spending environment is dependent upon the lifting of budgetary constraints on defense spending
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Similarly, since 2007, business jet manufacturing has declined due to the economic downturn in 2008, and demand from our business jet customers followed a similar trend
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Revenues from our military and defense and business jet customers combined have declined approximately 20% since 2012.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Although we expect
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	continued weak demand from our business jet manufacturing customers in 2016 and 2017, we do expect a significant upswing in 2018 as numerous new business jet aircraft types enter into service.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Other factors expected to affect the industries served by ASG include long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;term growth in worldwide fleet of passenger aircraft, an increase in the size of the existing installed base, aging of existing fleet and an expected improvement in the business jet market.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Energy Services Group
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The oil and gas industry has historically been both cyclical and seasonal. Activity levels are driven primarily by drilling rig counts,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	technological advances,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	well completions and workover activity, the geological characteristics of the producing wells and their effect on the services required to commence and maintain production levels, and our customers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	capital and operating budgets. All of these indicators are driven by commodity prices, which are affected by both domestic and global supply and demand factors. In particular, while U.S. natural gas prices are correlated with global oil price movements, they are also affected by local weather and consumption patterns.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	While global supply and demand factors will continue to result in commodity price volatility, we believe the secular outlook for the on-shore North American oil and gas industry remains positive due to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The projected long term growth in global energy demand.
</FONT>

</P>

<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Almost all E&amp;P companies outsource the services required by them to drill wells and maintain production. Drilling and completion activities require numerous services and products from time to time on an &#x201C;as needed&#x201D; basis.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>

</TABLE>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The decline of conventional North American oil and natural gas reservoirs, together with the development of new recovery technologies, is leading to a shift toward the drilling and development of onshore unconventional oil and natural gas resources that require more wells to be drilled and active maintenance to sustain production and maximize total recoveries. We believe drilling activity will
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	continue to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	be negatively impacted until energy supply and demand reach equilibrium and commodity prices stabilize at a level where our customers can achieve an appropriate return on their investments. However, we believe the increased requirements of these unconventional resources will lead to continued service activity while the industry rebalances its allocation of assets to meet future growth.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

	&#xB7;

<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Technologically driven breakthroughs, including (i)&nbsp;continued drilling activity supported by unconventional resources, (ii)&nbsp;the expanding use of horizontal drilling techniques and (iii)&nbsp;longer lateral lengths and increasing number of stages per well, have all created growing demand for services and products to support these advanced drilling activities, many of which are in remote areas with harsh environments.
</FONT>
</P>

<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">

<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The increasing complexity of technology used in the oil and natural gas exploration and development process requires additional technicians on location during drilling. In particular, the increasing trend of pursuing horizontal and directional wells as opposed to vertical wells requires additional expertise on location and, typically, longer drilling times.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Other factors expected to affect the industry served by our ESG segment include:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Growing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Demand for Natural Gas in the United States.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;We believe that natural gas will be in increasingly high deman
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	d in the United States over time because of its growing popularity as a cleaner burning fuel.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	While demand for natural gas during Fiscal 2015 declined due to unseasonably warm weather in the Northeast U.S. and the lack of infrastructure to efficiently transport natural gas to major markets on the East Coast, the ongoing shift to the use of natural gas from coal-fired power plants and the increased access to residential customers from new pipeline projects is expected to support increased demand for natural gas in the Northeast and Midwest states. In addition, the recent commencement of liquefied natural gas shipments from the United States to foreign markets is also expected to increase demand for natural gas production.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Continued Outsourcing of Ancillary Services.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;Some of the services we provide have been historically handled by drilling contractors themselves. In many instances, these services are only ancillary to the primary activity of drilling and completing wells and represent only a minor portion of the total well drilling cost.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	D
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	rilling contractors
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	often elect
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to outsource these services to suppliers who have the expertise to be able to provide increasingly more complex, high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality and reliable services on a 24/7 basis.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Products and Services

	We conduct our business through two operating segments: ASG and ESG. Information about each of our operating segments is included below.

	suppliers to support manufacturing customers under long term agreements. We stock over

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

The supplier will ship the parts directly to the customer by the date requested, eliminating a process queue and thus allowing for a database to be built over time. Products are stocked based on historical usage and forecasts. Through this process, we become the single point of contact for multiple approved suppliers to reduce our customers
</FONT>

	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	inventory and supplier base. Furthermore, we are able to offer a seamless order and billing process, while allowing full traceability of parts.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#KLX-20160131X10K_HTM_TOC">

	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Energy Services Group
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We serve energy industry customers who focus on developing and producing oil and gas onshore in North America. We have integrated the operations of the seven acquisitions that comprise our current business and manage them both by service and product line offerings and by geographic markets. We offer a variety of services both individually and on a bundled basis as requested by our customers. Our E&amp;P customers require numerous technical services and products on an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	as needed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	basis, including wireline services, fishing (retrieval) services and equipment,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	down-hole production services,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	pressure control, logging, pipe recovery and rental equipment to support these services. Much like the need for just
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;time delivery of consumables by ASG, ESG often is faced with just
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;time support requirements for our E&amp;P customers that may be experiencing critical operating issues such as servicing an operating well under high pressures, or removing blockages during well drilling or production. As a result, our industry specialists (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	many with over 40&nbsp;years of experience) are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and may be
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;call (on a rotational basis)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	24&nbsp;hours a day, 7&nbsp;days a week to meet our customers&#x2019; needs.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In the year ended December 31, 2014, the potential market for the services we provide expanded dramatically due to the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	technological advancements that allow for oil and gas recovery from previously unrecoverable shale
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	formations.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	However, Fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	was one of the most difficult years ever for the global oil and gas industry. Plummeting commodity prices driven by excess global supply resulted in record reductions in spending by all of our customers, as the domestic onshore drilling rig count was cut by approximately 75 percent from 1,744 rigs to 473 rigs, currently. In response to this dramatic reduction in activity, essentially all companies engaged in oil and gas exploration, production and support services have experienced significant reductions in revenues and profitability resulting in billions of dollars of impairment charges. The ensuing deep cuts in capital spending have resulted in severely negative impacts on both volume and pricing, and as a result
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	essentially all industry participants have implemented
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	massive
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	cuts in headcount and spending. Market conditions continued to worsen throughout the year and into 2016 and are currently at levels of activity and pricing which are unsustainable. In fact, through our fiscal year end, there have been 45 bankruptcies, wi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	th more expected in 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We initiated our expansion in th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	e U.S. onshore oil field services sector
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in August 2013 when we acquired the assets of Blue Dot Energy Services, LLC, a provider of on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;site services and rental equipment to exploration and production companies in the oil and gas industry with operations primarily in the Marcellus/Utica Shales. In December 2013, we acquired the assets of Bulldog Frac Rentals, LLC, an Eagle Ford Shale
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based provider of high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality pressure control valves and related rental equipment, operating primarily in the Eagle Ford and the Marcellus/Utica Shales. In January 2014, we acquired the assets of the LT Energy Services group of companies, an Eagle Ford Shale
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based provider of accommodation and related surface equipment. In February 2014, we acquired the assets of Wildcat Wireline LLC, a provider of wireline services primarily in the Eagle Ford and Marcellus/Utica Shales. In April 2014, we acquired the assets of Vision Oil Tools,&nbsp;LLC, an established provider of services and rental equipment to oil and gas E&amp;P companies with operations located in the Bakken Shale formation in North Dakota (Williston Basin), the Piceance and DJ Basins in Colorado, the Permian Basin in Texas and in Wyoming. In April 2014, we acquired the assets of the Marcellus Gasfield Services group of companies, an oilfield support services and associated rental equipment business based in the northeast U.S. In June 2014, we acquired the assets of the Cornell Solutions group of companies, an oilfield support services and associated rental equipment busin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ess based in the southwest U.S.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As a result of these acquisitions, we have established a solid presence in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	all the major onshore oil and gas producing regions in the contiguous 48 states (other than California), including
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the Northeast (Marcellus and Utica Shales), Rocky Mountains (Williston, DJ and Piceance Basins), Southwest (Permian Basin and Eagle Ford) and Mid
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Continent regions in North America. We serve energy industry customers who focus on developing and producing oil and gas onshore in North America. We have integrated the operations of the seven acquisitions that comprise our current business and manage them by both service and product line offerings and by geographic markets. We provide high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality services and products (new and remanufactured after use and American Petroleum Institute (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	API
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	) certified) to remote drilling sites using our manufacturing, certification, logistics and IT capabilities to properly prepare for deployment, store, locate and deliver
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our equipment and service teams
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, as needed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to support our customers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	drilling operations.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We also have a growing in-house proprietary tool development team which is focused on designing innovative tools that will further differentiate our services and enhance the outcomes for our customers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

	8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We offer a variety of complementary services, both individually and on a bundled basis, as requested by our customers.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our key service and product offerings include:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Onshore Completion Services:&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Includes a variety of services and equipment related to the initial well stimulation, completion and production. These services include the placement and removal of flow control nipples and valves, completion packers, bridge plugs and composite flow through frac plugs, as well as a full line of downhole services tools to optimize oil and gas recovery. These tools and services coupled with our expertise assist our clients in performing operations to optimize oil and gas recovery.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	These services and equipment are utilized in both the completion of newly drilled wells and the completion of behind pipe reserves in wells which have been previously drilled but not completed.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Wireline Services:&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our wireline services are provided through mobile units that contain large spools of wire. This large spool of wire will spool and unspool, which in turn allows tools and equipment to be quickly conveyed in and out of a wellbore. These wireline units and personnel provide a variety of different downhole services. These services include composite frac plug pump downs, pipe recovery and perforation, as well as well evaluation and logging services.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Fishing Services and Tools:&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our fishing tool business provides a range of specialized services and equipment that is utilized on a non-routine basis for both drilling and well services operations. When intervention is required at the well site, we provide solutions for our customers. When downhole problems develop and drilling or services operations or conditions require non-routine intervention, technicians intervene with specialized tools that are specifically suited to retrieve, or &#x201C;fish,&#x201D; and remove trapped equipment. This equipment may include
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	overshots, spears, jarring equipment, internal and external cutters, Venturi tools, magnets and wash over equipment. In addition to our fishing services, we also provide drill
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;out services to our clients consisting of downhole motors used to drill out frac plugs and sliding sleeves.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">

<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Down-hole Completion and Production Services:
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;Downhole production services utilize a wide range of tools consisting of packers, bridge plugs, wellbore clean out equipment and cementation equipment to provide services to the completion and work-over market.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Pressure Control:&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We offer a full line of pressure control services and rental equipment to assist our clients at the wellsite. When a client moves on a well to perform
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	completion or production activities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, they are required to have some means of containing the pressure of the wellbore. Through the use of frac stacks, pressure valves and blow out preventers properly sized for the operation, operators are able to contain any release of pressure from the wellbore. We provide a full line of hydraulic and manual equipment, as well as services to keep them in proper working condition. We service this equipment at our operations facilities to ensure our equipment performs at the wellsite. As part of this service, we also provide rental pipe, power swivels, reverse units and other equipment used to perform well service operations.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

Our turnkey solutions can be designed for complex requirements, conditions and personnel. We provide a comprehensive range of value
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Remanufacturing Shop:&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our operations facilities are positioned around the U.S. and allow our personnel to properly service, restore and test all pressure control equipment, valves, choke manifolds and closing units. By properly servicing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and re-certifying
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our equipment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	we can ensure our equipment works when it is deployed to a wellsite. In several of the operations facilities, we also offer machine shop services, which consist of CNC lathes, milling machines, spindle lathes and other machining equipment to rework and rectify damaged equipment and to design/build specialized fit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;purpose tools.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe that ESG offers services and products which create value for our customers by reducing their exposure to non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;productive time (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	NPT
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	) during the drilling and production phases. We provide services and equipment that assist our customers with maintaining and increasing the permeability of the reservoir. We provide specialized experts and equipment to locate and remove blockages or lost equipment from the reservoir that impede drilling or production operations and a broad range of rental equipment to support the operations of our service personnel and our customers.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We provide essentially all of our services and related rental equipment in all of our geo regions, providing consistency for our customers and the ability to manage our business on a best practices basis throughout the organization
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Customers, Competition and Marketing
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Aerospace Solutions Group
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We market our aerospace fasteners and other consumables directly to the airlines, aircraft leasing companies, MRO providers, general aviation, first
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;tier suppliers to the commercial, military and defense airframe manufacturers, the airframe manufacturers and other distributors. We believe that our key competitive advantages are the breadth of our product offerings and our ability to deliver our products on a timely basis, combined with our core competencies in information management, purchasing and logistics management. Customers for our ASG segment include all major commercial aircraft, business jet and military OEMs, aftermarket MRO providers and airlines.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Approximately 53
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% of our ASG revenues in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to customers in the U.S. with 29
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% to customers in Europe and the balance to customers in Asia, the Pacific and the Middle East.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe the principal competitive factors in our industry include the ability to provide superior customer service and support, on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;time delivery, sufficient inventory availability, competitive pricing and an effective quality assurance program. Our competitors include both U.S. and foreign companies. Our largest competitors include Wesco Aircraft, Pattonair, Align, AAA, Adept, Herndon, Boeing, Airbus, PCC, Alcoa, Wencor, Champion, Heico, Jamaica Bearings, Avnet and Avio.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	50
</FONT>

	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sales
</FONT>

	, marketing, product support and customer service
</FONT>

	personnel with an average of over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years of experience at our ASG segment. Our sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	professionals as of that date were loca
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ted mostly in the United States
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Energy Services Group
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ESG provides services and products and competes in a variety of distinct sub
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;segments with a number of competitors. Substantially all of our ESG customers are engaged in the energy industry. Most of our sales are to regional or independent oil companies and these sales have resulted in a diversified and geographically b
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	alanced portfolio of more than 4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

	Warranty Product Liability, Insurance
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Aerospace Solutions Group
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We warrant our ASG products, or specific
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	components thereof, for periods ranging from one to three years, depending on product and component type. We receive appropriate product warranties and certifications from the manufacturer, and in the event of a defective part, we look to the manufacturer for reimbursement. Historically
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, warranty costs have not been material at ASG.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Energy Services Group
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The use of certain of our ESG rental equipment or the provision of technical services in connection therewith could involve operational risk and thereby expose us to liabilities. An accident involving our services or equipment, or the failure of a product, could result in personal injury, loss of life and damage to property, equipment or the environment. Damages from a catastrophic occurrence, such as a fire or explosion, could result in substantial claims for damages. We generally attempt to negotiate the terms of our MSAs consistent with industry practice. In general, we attempt to take responsibility for our own personnel and property, while our customers, such as the E&amp;P companies and well operators, take responsibility for their own personnel, property and all liabilities arising from well and subsurface operations. Given the nature of the services and equipment we provide to our customers, none of our businesses have incurred any significant losses as a result of a claim for damages arising from the use of our services or products, either individually or in the aggregate.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We maintain a risk management program that covers operating hazards, including product liability, property damage and personal injury claims as well as certain limited environmental claims. Our risk management program includes primary and excess umbrella liability policies of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million per occurrence, including sudden and accidental pollution claims. We believe that our insurance is sufficient to cover product liability claims.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our information technology infrastructure is based on a proprietary
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	application that has been highly customized for the aerospace consumables management business over the last 20&nbsp;years. Our IT systems supp
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ort our order
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;cash, procure
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;pay, warehouse management and accounting processes on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a global basis. Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	key proprietary IT
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	application interfaces with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our customized proprietary applications together with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	leading specialty software packages such as JDA (Demand Planning), Sterling (EDI) and Oracle (Business Intelligence, Financial Consolidations and Financial Reporting).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	During 2015, we implemented a Microsoft-based enterprise resource planning (&#x201C;ERP&#x201D;) system to support our ASG, ESG and Corporate activities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We also employ virtualization technology to increase system availability, reduce hardware and maintenance costs and respond efficiently to market dynamics. Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	systems are largely hosted on Microsoft &#x201C;Cloud&#x201D; platforms as well as a stand-alone
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	data services infrastructure
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	runs 24/7 and is protected by network security technologies, an uninterrupted power supply and a backup generator. Remote access to our systems is provided via separate, high speed connections.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Energy Services Group
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	successfully integrated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our acquisitions onto a single
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	financial accounting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	platform using
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the aforementioned ERP system together with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	an industry leading rental asset management software
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	TrakQuip
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	These IT systems
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	provide us with a scalable integrated platform that facilitates highly efficient operations, consolidated invoicing and optimal equipment utilization
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	on both
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a site and segment basis.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our operating strategy is based upon balancing high asset and personnel utilization levels with consistently superior customer service. As such, our IT systems are integral to effectively managing our business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	Aerospace Solutions Group
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	FAA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	), prescribe standards for aircraft components, including virtually all commercial airline and general aviation products, as well as regulations regarding the repair and overhaul of airframes, equipment and engines. Specific regulations vary from country to country, although compliance with FAA requirements generally satisfies regulatory requirements in other countries. In addition, the products we distribute must also be certified by aircraft and engine OEMs.&nbsp;If any of the material authorizations or approvals that allow us to supply products are revoked or suspended, then the sale of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

	related products would be prohibited by law, which would have an adverse effect on our business, financial condition and results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	From time to time, the FAA or equivalent regulatory agencies in other countries propose new regulations or changes to existing regulations, which are usually more stringent than existing regulations. If these proposed regulations are adopted and enacted, we could incur significant additional costs to achieve compliance, which could have a material adverse effect on our business, financial condition and results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We are also subject to other government rules and regulations that include the Foreign Corrupt Practices Act of 1977, as amended, International Traffic in Arms Regulations and the False Claims Act.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Energy Services Group
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our ESG operations are subject to extensive and changing federal, state and local laws and regulations establishing health, safety and environmental quality standards, including those governing discharges of pollutants into the air and water and the management and disposal of hazardous substances and wastes. We may be subject to liabilities or penalties for violations of those regulations. We are also subject to laws and regulations, such as the Federal Superfund Law and similar state statutes, governing remediation of contamination which could occur or might have occurred at facilities that we own or operate, or which we formerly owned or operated, or to which we send or have sent hazardous substances or wastes for treatment, recycling or disposal. We believe that we are currently compliant, in all material respects, with applicable environmental laws and regulations. However, we could become subject to future liabilities or obligations as a result of new or more stringent interpretations of existing laws and regulations. In addition, we may have liabilities or obligations in the future if we discover any environmental contamination or liability relating to our facilities or operations.
</FONT>
</P>

<EFX_RISK_FACTORS>
<A NAME="FIS_RISK_FACTORS"></A>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ITEM 1A.&nbsp;&nbsp;RISK FACTOR
</FONT>
<A NAME="KLX-20160131X10K_HTM_ITEM1ARISKFACTORS_79490">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	S
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	You should carefully consider each of the following risks and uncertainties, which we believe are the principal risks that we face and of which we are currently aware, and all of the other information in this Form&nbsp;10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;K. Some of the risks and uncertainties described below relate to our business, while others relate to the spin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;off. Other risks relate principally to the securities markets and ownership of our common stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	If any of the following events actually occur, our business, financial condition or financial results could be materially adversely affected, the trading price of our common stock could decline and you could lose all or part of your investment. Additional risks and uncertainties that we do not presently know about or currently believe are not material may also adversely affect our business and operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Risks Relating to Our Business
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Risks Relating to the Aerospace Solutions Business
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We sell products to the airline industry, which is a heavily regulated industry, and the ASG business may be adversely affected if our suppliers or customers lose government approvals, if more stringent government regulations are enacted or if industry oversight is increased.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The FAA prescribes standards and licensing requirements for aircraft components, including virtually all commercial airline and general aviation cabin interior products, and licenses component repair stations within the United States. Comparable agencies, such as the European Aviation Safety Agency, the Civil Aviation Administration of China and the Japanese Civil Aviation Board, regulate these matters in other countries. Our suppliers and customers must generally be certified by such governmental agencies. If any of our suppliers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	government certifications are revoked, we would be less likely to buy such supplier
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s products and, as a result, would need to locate a suitable alternate supply of such products, which we may be unable to accomplish on commercially reasonable terms or at all. If any of our customers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	government certifications are revoked, their demand for the products we sell would decline. In each case, ASG
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s results of operations and financial condition may be adversely affected.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	From time to time, these regulatory agencies propose new regulations or heighten industry oversight. These new regulations generally cause an increase in costs of our suppliers and customers to comply with these regulations. In the case of our suppliers, these expenses may be passed on to us in the form of price increases, which we may be unable to pass along to our customers. In the case of our customers, these expenses may limit their ability to purchase products from us. In each case, ASG
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s results of operations and financial condition may be adversely affected.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
