<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#KLX-20160131X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	two implementation approaches, either prospectively to all awards granted or modified after the effective date, or retrospectively to all awards with performance targets that are outstanding as of the beginning of the earliest annual period presented in the financial statements and to all new or modified awards thereafter. The adoption of ASU 2014-12 is not expected to have a material impact on the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In May 2014, FASB issued ASU 2014-09, Revenue from Contracts with Customers, which updated the guidance in ASC Topic 606, Revenue Recognition. The core principle of the guidance is that an entity should recognize revenue to depict the transfer of promised goods or services to customers in an amount that reflects the consideration to which the entity expects to be entitled in exchange for those goods or services. To achieve that core principle, an entity should identify the contract(s) with a customer, identify the performance obligations in the contract, determine the transaction price, allocate the transaction price to the performance obligations in the contract and recognize revenue when (or as) the entity satisfies a performance obligation. In August 2015, the FASB issued ASU 2015-14, Revenue from Contracts with Customers (Topic 606): Deferral of the Effective Date. The amendments in this update deferred the effective date for implementation of ASU 2014-09 by one year and is now effective for annual reporting periods beginning after December 15, 2017. Early application is permitted only as of annual reporting periods beginning after December 15, 2016 including interim reporting periods within that period. The Company is currently evaluating the impact this guidance will have on its consolidated financial condition, results of operations, cash flows and disclosures and is currently unable to estimate the impact of adopting this guidance.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	2. BUSINESS COMBINATIONS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	During 2013, the Company acquired the assets of Blue Dot Energy Services,&nbsp;LLC (&#x201C;Blue Dot&#x201D;) and Bulldog Frac Rentals,&nbsp;LLC (&#x201C;Bulldog&#x201D;) (the &#x201C;2013 Acquisitions&#x201D;), providers of parts distribution, rental equipment and on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;site services to the oil and gas industry, for a net purchase price of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$114.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. The excess of the purchase price over the fair value of the identifiable assets acquired approximated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$70.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, of which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$33.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	was allocated to identified intangible assets, consisting of customer contracts and relationships and covenants not to compete, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$37.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	was included in goodwill. The useful life assigned to the customer contracts and relationships was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	20
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years, and the covenants not to compete were being amortized over their contractual periods of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years. The customer contracts and relationships and the covenants not to compete were both impaired and fully written off during the third quarter of 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. See N
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ote 4 for a discussion of the asset impairment charge.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In January 2014, the Company acquired the assets of the LT Energy Services group of companies ("LT"), an Eagle Ford Shale provider of rental equipment, for a net purchase price of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$102.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. In February 2014, the Company acquired the assets of Wildcat Wireline LLC ("Wildcat"), a provider of wireline services primarily in the Eagle Ford Shale and also in the Marcellus/Utica Shales, for a net purchase price of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$153.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. In April 2014, the Company acquired the assets of the Vision Oil Tools, LLC group of companies ("Vision"), a provider of technical services and associated rental equipment to the energy sector. Vision established a new geographical base of operations for the Company in the North Dakota (Williston/Bakken) and Rocky Mountain regions. The t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	otal purchase price was

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$175.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	which included a deferred payment of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$35.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, which was paid during the first quarter of Fiscal 2015 based on the achievement of 2014 financial results. In April 2014, the Company acquired the assets of the Marcellus Gasfield Services group of companies ("MGS") engaged in manufacturing and rental of equipment in the Marcellus/Utica Shales for approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$44.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. During June 2014, the Company acquired the assets of the Cornell Solutions group of companies ("Cornell"), which provides technical services and rental equipment to the energy sector in the Eagle Ford Shale and Permian Basin. The total purchase price was

	$128.2

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Amortization expense of intangible assets was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$23.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$30.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$19.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$2.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for the years ended January 31, 2016, December 31, 2014 and 2013
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and the one month ended January 31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, respectively
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Amortization expense is expected to be approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$15.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	each
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	next
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In accordance with ASC 350, goodwill is not amortized but is subject to an annual impairment test.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The continued downturn in the oil and gas industry, including the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	nearly 75%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	decrease in the number of onshore drilling rigs and the resulting significant cutbacks in the capital expenditures of our customers, represented a significant adverse change in the business climate, which indicated that the ESG reporting unit&#x2019;s goodwill
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	impaired and ESG asset
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	group&#x2019;s long-lived assets may not be recoverable. As a result, during the third quarter ended October 31, 2015, the Company performed an interim goodwill impairment test and a long-lived asset recoverability test. The results of the goodwill impairment testing indicated that goodwill was impaired which resulted in a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$310.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	goodwill impairment charge for the year ended January 31, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Long-lived assets, such as property and equipment and purchased intangibles subject to amortization, are tested for impairment when there is evidence that events or changes in circumstances indicate that the carrying amount of an asset may not be recovered. An impairment loss is recognized when the undiscounted cash flows expected to be generated by an asset (or group of assets) is less than its carrying amount. Any required impairment loss is measured as the amount by which the asset&#x2019;s carrying value exceeds its fair value and is recorded as a reduction in the carrying value of the related asset and a charge to operating results. Based on the impairment indicators above, we performed a long-lived asset impairment analysis and concluded the carrying amount of the long-lived assets exceeded the undiscounted cash flows of the ESG asset group. As a result, we recorded a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$329.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	long-lived asset impairment charge,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$177.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	related to identified intangible assets and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$152.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	related to property and equipment for the year ended January 31, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

	3

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, respectively. These amounts include costs for functions including executive management, finance, legal, information technology, human resources, employee benefits administration, treasury, risk management, procurement and other shared services.
</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In December 2014, in connection with the Spin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;off, the Company issued
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1,200.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	aggregate principal amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5.875%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	senior unsecured notes due 2022 (the &#x201C;5.875% Notes&#x201D;), in an offering pursuant to the Securities Act of 1933, as amended. The net proceeds from the issuance of the 5.875% Notes were approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1,172.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, of which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$750.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	was distributed to Former Parent, leaving KLX with net proceeds of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$422.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. The 5.875%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Notes are senior unsecured debt obligations of the Company. We also entered into a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$750.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	secured revolving credit facility
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	dated as of December 16, 2014 and amended May 19, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(the &#x201C;Revolving Credit Facility&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	January 31, 2016 and December 31, 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;term debt consisted of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1,200.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of our 5.875% Notes.
</FONT>
</P>

	Letters of credit outstanding under the Revolving Credit Facility aggregated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Revolving Credit Facility
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is tied to a borrowing base formula and has no financial covenants. The Revolving Credit Facility
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	bears interest at an annual rate equal to the London interbank offered rate (&#x201C;LIBOR&#x201D;) plus the applicable margin (as defined), and expires in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	May 2020
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	No
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	amounts
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	were outstanding under the Revolving Credit Facility as of
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. COMMITMENTS, CONTINGENCIES AND OFF
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#8209;BALANCE
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#8209;SHEET ARRANGEMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Lease Commitments
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2014;The Company finances its use of certain facilities and equipment under committed lease arrangements provided by various institutions. Since the terms of these arrangements meet the accounting definition of operating lease arrangements, the aggregate sum of future minimum lease payments is not reflected on the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	consolidated and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	combined balance sheets. At
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	January 31, 2016

	, future minimum lease payments under these arrangements approximated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$87.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, of which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$83.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is related to long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;term real estate leases.
</FONT>

</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Litigation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2014;The Company is a defendant in various legal actions arising in the normal course of business, the outcomes of which, in the opinion of management, neither individually nor in the aggregate are likely to result in a material adverse effect on the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	consolidated and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	combined financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On January 6, 2016, a putative class action complaint was filed against us and certain of our executive officers and directors in the United States District Court for the Southern District of Florida. The named plaintiff seeks to represent a class of purchasers of our common stock during the period from March 9, 2015 to November 11, 2015. The complaint alleges violations of Section 10(b) of the Exchange Act and Rule 10b-5 promulgated thereunder, as well as, in the case of the individual defendants, the control person provisions of the Exchange Act. The complaint principally alleges that the defendants knowingly made incorrect statements regarding the value of the identifiable intangible assets and goodwill associated with ESG prior to the impairment of such assets during the third quarter of 2015. The complaint seeks unspecified damages, interest and attorneys' fees. We believe the claims are without merit and intend vigorously to defend ourselves against them, including by promptly seeking dismissal of the complaint.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Indemnities, Commitments and Guarantees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2014;During its normal course of business, the Company has made certain indemnities, commitments and guarantees under which it may be required to make payments in relation to certain transactions. These indemnities include indemnities to various lessors in connection with facility leases for certain claims arising from such facility or lease and indemnities to other parties to certain acquisition agreements. The duration of these indemnities, commitments and guarantees varies, and in certain cases, is indefinite. Many of these indemnities, commitments and guarantees provide for limitations on the maximum potential future payments the Company could be obligated to make. However, the Company is unable to estimate the maximum amount of liability related to its indemnities, commitments and guarantees because such liabilities are contingent upon the occurrence of events that are not reasonably determinable. Management believes that any liability for these indemnities, commitments and guarantees would not be material to the accompanying
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	consolidated and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	combined financial statements. Accordingly, no significant amounts have been accrued for indemnities, commitments and guarantees.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company has employment agreements with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	year initial terms, which renew for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	additional year on each anniversary date, with certain key members of management. The Company&#x2019;s employment agreements generally provide for certain protections in the event of a change of control. These protections generally include the payment of severance and related benefits under certain circumstances in the event of a change of control and for the Company to reimburse such officers for the amount of any excise taxes associated with such be
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	nefits.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#KLX-20160131X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>

</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	9. INCOME TAXES
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Income taxes as presented are calculated o
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	n a separate tax return basis.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company determined the provision for income taxes using the asset and liability approach. Under this approach, deferred income taxes represent the expected future tax consequences of temporary differences between the carrying amounts and tax basis of assets and liabilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Valuation allowances are established when necessary to reduce deferred tax assets to the amounts expected to be realized. In assessing the need for a valuation allowance, the Company looked to the future reversal of existing taxable temporary differences, taxable income in carryback years and the feasibility of tax planning strategies and estimated future taxable income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The need for a valuation allowance can be affected by changes to tax laws, changes to statutory tax rates and changes to fu
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ture
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	taxable income estimates.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company recognizes tax benefits from uncertain tax positions only if it is more likely than not that the tax position will be sustained on examination by the taxing authorities, based on the technical merits of the position. The tax benefits recognized in the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	consolidated and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	combined financial statements from such positions are measured based on the largest benefit that has a greater than 50% likelihood of being realized upon ultimate settlement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As of January 31, 2016, the Company has recorded a tax indemnity payable to B/E Aerospace totaling
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$6.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, of which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is classified in other current liabilities and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$4.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is classified in other long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;term liabilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company does not anticipate that the total unrecognized tax benefits will significantly change due to the settlement of audits or the expiration of statutes of limitation within twelve months of this reporting date. The Company classifies interest and penalties related to income tax as income tax expense. The amount included in the Company&#x2019;s liability for unrecognized tax benefits for interest and penalties was immaterial as of January 31, 2016, January 31, 2015 and December 31, 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company is subject to taxation in the United States, various states and foreign jurisdictions. The Company has significant operations in the United States, the United Kingdom, France and Germany. Tax years that remain subject to examinations by major tax jurisdictions vary by legal entity but are generally open outside the U.S. for the tax years ending after 2009.
</FONT>

	practical to determine the amount of U.S. income and foreign withholding tax payable in the event all such foreign earnings are repatriated.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company&#x2019;s effective tax rate can fluctuate as operations and the local country tax rates fluctuate due to the number of tax jurisdictions in which the Company operates.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Under the tax sharing and indemnity agreement between the Company and B/E Aerospace, B/E Aerospace generally assumes liability for all federal and state income taxes for all tax
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	periods ending on or prior to December
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. B/E Aerospace assumes the liability for all federal and state income taxes of KLX&#x2019;s U.S. operations through the distribution date. KLX assumes all other federal taxes, foreign income tax/non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;income taxes and state/local non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;income taxes related to its business for all periods and B/E Aerospace assumes all other federal taxes, foreign income tax/non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;income taxes and state/local non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;income taxes related to their business for all periods. Additional taxes incurred related to the internal restructuring to separate the businesses to complete the spin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;off shall be shared equally between B/E Aerospace and KLX. Taxes incurred related to certain international tax initiatives for the KLX business shall be assumed by KLX subject to the calculation provisions of the tax sharing and indemnity agreement. In addition, B/E Aerospace transferred to KLX all the deferred tax assets and liabilities related to the KLX business as of December&nbsp;16, 2014.
</FONT>
</P>

	. EMPLOYEE RETIREMENT PLANS

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	B/E Aerospace
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sponsored and contributes to a qualified, defined contribution savings and investment plan, covering substantially all U.S. employees, including current KLX employees that transferred to KLX from B/E Aerospace. Balances related to the Company employees&#x2019; participation in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	B/E Aerospace&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	plans were determined by specifically identifying the balances for the Company&#x2019;s participants. The B/E Aerospace,&nbsp;Inc. Savings Plan was established pursuant to Section&nbsp;401(k) of the Internal Revenue Code. Under the terms of this plan, covered employees could contribute up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	100%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of their pay, limited to certain statutory maximum contributions for 2014 and 2013. Participants are vested in matching contributions immediately and the matching percentage is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	100%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the first
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of employee contributions and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	on the next
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of employee contributions. Total expense for the plan was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$3.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$2.8,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;

	$1.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;

	$0.4

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for the years ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	January 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	December 31, 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3 &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and the one month ended January 31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, respectively
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	B/E Aerospace
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	also sponsored and contributed to a supplemental executive retirement plan (&#x201C;SERP&#x201D;), which was established pursuant to Section&nbsp;409A of the Internal Revenue Code, for certain B/E Aerospace and Company employees. The SERP is an unfunded plan maintained for the purpose of providing deferred compensation for certain employees. This plan allows certain employees to annually elect to defer a portion of their compensation, on a pre
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;tax basis, until their retirement. The retirement benefit to be provided is based on the amount of compensation deferred. The Former Parent made cash matching contributions and earnings on deferrals at various levels, which varies by position. Compensation expense under this program was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$2.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and

	$0.2

	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3, respectively

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Compensation expense was immaterial under this program for the one month ended January 31, 2015.

	The Company and its subsidiaries participate in government
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	11. STOCKHOLDERS&#x2019; EQUITY
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Earnings Per Share
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2014;Basic net earnings per common share is computed using the weighted average of common shares outstanding during the year. Diluted net earnings per common share reflects the potential dilution from assumed conversion of all dilutive securities such as stock options and unvested restricted stock using the treasury stock method. When the effects of the outstanding stock options, restricted stock awards or restricted stock units are anti
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;dilutive, they are not included in the calculation of diluted earnings per common share. For the years ended January 31, 2016, December 31, 2014 and 2013 and the one month ended January 31, 2015,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	shares and approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million shares, respectively, were excluded from the determination of diluted earnings per common share because the effect would have been anti
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;dilutive.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	On December&nbsp;16, 2014, the distribution date, B/E Aerospace stockholders of record as of the close of business on December&nbsp;5, 2014 received
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	share of KLX common stock for every two shares of B/E Aerospace&#x2019;s common stock held as of the record date. Basic and diluted earnings per common share and the average number of common shares outstanding were calculated using the number of KLX common shares outstanding immediately following the distribution.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;Term Incentive Plan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2014;B/E Aerospace has a Long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Term Incentive Plan (&#x201C;LTIP&#x201D;) under which the Former Parent&#x2019;s Compensation Committee may grant stock options, stock appreciation rights, restricted stock, restricted stock units or other forms of equity based or equity related awards. KLX adopted an LTIP similar to the Former Parent&#x2019;s upon the Spin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;off, and unvested shares in the Former Parent were transferred with the employees to KLX on the same terms and conditions on an exchange ratio of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1.8139
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	such that the impact was neutral to employees at the date of the Spin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;off.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	During 2014, 2013 and 2012, B/E Aerospace granted restricted stock under the LTIP to certain members of the Company&#x2019;s management. Restricted stock grants vest over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	four
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years and are granted at the discretion of the Compensation Committee of the B/E Aerospace&#x2019;s Board of Directors. Certain awards also vest upon attainment of performance goals. Compensation cost is recorded on a straight
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;line basis over the vesting term of the shares based on the grant date value using the closing trading price. Share based compensation of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$11.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$3.5,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$3.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	was recorded during fiscal year 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, 2014 and 2013 and the one month ended January 31, 2015, respectively. Unrecognized compensation cost related to these grants was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$36.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	at January 31, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

</TD>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:18PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:18PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 18.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	(1)
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Aggregate intrinsic value is calculated based on the difference between our closing stock price at year end and the exercise price, multiplied by the number of in-the-money options and represents the pre-tax amount that would have been received by the option holders, had they all exercised all their options on the fiscal year end date.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	For the year ended January 31, 2016 and the one month ended January 31, 2015, we recorded
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$3.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, respectively, of stock-based compensation expense related to these options that is included within selling, general and administrative expenses. At January 31, 2016 and January 31, 2015, the unrecognized stock-based compensation related to these options was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$7.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$11.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, respectively, and is expected to be recognized over a weighted-average period of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1.87
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2.87
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We use the Black-Scholes option pricing model to determine the fair value of stock options. The determination of the fair value of stock-based payment awards on the date of grant using an option-pricing model is affected by our stock price as well as assumptions regarding complex and subjective variables. These variables include the expected stock price volatility over the term of the awards, risk-free interest rate and expected dividends.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Due to the limited trading history of our common stock, we estimated expected volatility based on historical data of comparable public companies. The expected term, which represents the period of time that options granted are expected to be outstanding, is estimated based on guidelines provided in U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission Staff Accounting Bulletin No. 110 and represents the average of the vesting tranches and contractual terms. The risk-free rate assumed in valuing the options is based on the U.S. Treasury rate in effect at the time of grant for the expected term of the option. We do not anticipate paying any cash dividends in the foreseeable future and, therefore, used an expected dividend yield of zero in the option pricing model. Compensation expense is recognized only for those options expected to vest with forfeitures estimated based on our historical experience at B/E Aerospace and future expectations. Stock-based compensation awards are amortized on a straight line basis over a three year period.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The weighted average assumptions used to value the option grants are as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the closing price on the last business day of each semi

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

	50,000

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

	.

	December 31, 2014

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and 201

	3

	. SEGMENT REPORTING

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company is organized based on the products and services it offers. As a result of the ESG acquisitions, the Company determined that ESG met the requirements of a reportable segment, and its operations during 2013 were n
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ot significant. The Company&#x2019;s A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	G
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	reportable segment, which is also its operating segment, is comprised of consumables management and is in a single line of business. The segment regularly reports its results of operations and makes requests for capital expenditures and acquisition funding to the Company&#x2019;s chief operational decision
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;making group. This group is comprised of the Chairman and Ch
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ief Executive Officer and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the President and Chief Operating Officer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.

	1

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. FAIR VALUE INFORMATION
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	All financial instruments are carried at amounts that approximate estimated fair value. The fair value is the price at which an asset could be exchanged in a current transaction between knowledgeable, willing parties. Assets measured at fair value are categorized based upon the lowest level of significant input to the valuations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Level&nbsp;1&#x2014;quoted prices in active markets for identical assets and liabilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Level&nbsp;2&#x2014;quoted prices for identical assets and liabilities in markets that are not active or observable inputs other than quoted prices in active markets for identical assets and liabilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Level&nbsp;3&#x2014;unobservable inputs in which there is little or no market data available, which require the reporting entity to develop its own assumptions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The carrying amounts of cash and cash equivalents (which the Company classifies as Level&nbsp;1 assets), accounts receivable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;trade and accounts payable represent their respective fair values due to their short
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;term nature. There was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	debt outstanding under the Revolving Credit Facility as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	January 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. The fair value of the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5.875%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Notes, based on market prices for publicly
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;traded debt (which the Company classifies as Level&nbsp;2 inputs), was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1,136.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1,182.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	January 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Goodwill and long-lived assets, including property and equipment and purchased intangibles subject to amortization were impaired and written down to their estimated fair values during the third quarter of Fiscal 2015. The goodwill level 3 fair value was determined using an income based approach utilizing estimates of future cash flow, discount rate and long-term growth rate, all of which were unobservable. The long-lived asset level 3 fair value was determined using a combination of the cost approach and the market approach, which used inputs that included replacement costs (unobservable), physical deterioration estimates (unobservable), economic obsolescence (unobservable), and market sales data for comparable assets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">

</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Net earnings per share are computed individually for each quarter presented. Therefore, the sum of the quarterly net earnings per share may not necessarily equal the total for the year.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(2) The Company has potential common stock equivalents related to its outstanding restricted stock awards, restricted stock units and employee stock purchase plan. These potential common stock equivalents were not included in diluted loss per share for the three months ended December 31, 2014 because the effect would have been anti-dilutive. Accordingly, basic and diluted loss per common share and the weighted average number of shares used in the computation are the same for the three months ended December 31, 2014. For each of the other periods presented, the Company had potential common stock equivalents related to its outstanding restricted stock awards, restricted stock units and employee stock purchase plan as of December 31, 2014 that were considered in the Company's diluted earnings per share calculation.
</FONT>
</P>

	(3) Net loss in the fourth quarter includes non-recurring costs, including acquisition and integration costs, severance, other Spin-off related costs and exit taxes related to a major international tax planning initiative aggregating approximately

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Agreement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;)

	&nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is entered into effective as of December 22, 2015, by and between KLX Inc., a Delaware corporation (the &#x201C;

	Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	RECITALS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:32.4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	WHEREAS, the Company and the Executive
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	previously entered into an Employment Agreement effective as of February 26, 2015 (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Prior Agreement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:32.4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	WHEREAS, concurrently with the execution of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Prior
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Agreement, the Executive and the Company entered into the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	KLX 2015 Proprietary Rights Agreement, (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	2015 Proprietary Rights Agreement

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

	attached hereto as

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:32.4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	WHEREAS, the Executive and the Company wish to amend and restate the Prior Agreement in its entirety in the manner set forth herein.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:32.4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	NOW, THEREFORE, for good and valuable consideration, the receipt and adequacy of which is hereby acknowledged, the parties hereto, each intending to be legally hound, do hereby agree as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	1.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Employment.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Unless otherwise terminated pursuant to the provisions of Section 4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or 5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	hereof, the Company shall employ the Executive and the Executive shall perform services for and continue in the employment of the Company commencing on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	February 26, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Effective Date
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	until the third anniversary of the Effective Date, and the Executive&#x2019;s employment hereunder shall automatically be extended on the first anniversary date of the Effective Date and on each subsequent anniversary of the Effective Date for additional one (1) year periods until either the Company or the Executive gives the other party at least thirty (30) days&#x2019; written notice prior to the anniversary of the Effective Date of any such year of its or his desire to not renew the then current term of this Agreement, unless the Executive&#x2019;s employment is terminated earlier pursuant to this Agreement as hereinafter set forth.&nbsp;&nbsp;For purposes of this Agreement, the term &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Employment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Term
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D; shall mean the initial three (3) year period and all extensions thereof, if any, as aforesaid, provided that the Executive continues to be employed by the Company; provided, however that for the purposes of Sections 4 and 5 of this Agreement, the Employment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Term
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	shall run through the last day of the then current Employment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Term
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(assuming for this purpose the Executive&#x2019;s continued employment through such last day).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Position and Duties.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Executive shall serve the Company in the capacity of Vice President and General Manager, Aerospace Solutions Group and shall be accountable to and shall have such other powers, duties and responsibilities, consistent with such capacity, as may from time to time be prescribed by the President or Chief Operating Officer of the Company, or his/their designee, in his/their sole discretion. The Executive shall perform and discharge, faithfully, diligently and to the best of his ability, such powers, duties and responsibilities and shall comply with all of the Company&#x2019;s policies and procedures. The Executive shall devote substantially all of his working time and efforts to the business and affairs of the Company.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Compensation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Salary.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	During the Employment Term, the Executive shall receive a salary (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Salary
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	payable at the rate of $360,08
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.00 per annum. Such rate shall be subject to adjustment from time to time by the Compensation Committee of the Board of Directors (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Compensation Committee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Salary shall be payable biweekly or in accordance with the Company&#x2019;s current payroll practices, less all required deductions. The Salary shall be pro-rated for any period of service less than a full year.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Incentive Bonus.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	During the Employment Term, the Executive shall be eligible to receive an incentive performance bonus of up to 75% of the Salary (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Target
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Bonus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	in accordance with the Company&#x2019;s executive bonus plan then in effect, as determined by the Compensation Committee at the end of the applicable fiscal year in its sole discretion. The incentive bonus, if any, shall be paid in accordance with Company policy, but in no event later than March 15th of the year following the year in which the Executive earned such bonus.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Expenses.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	During the Employment Term, the Executive shall be entitled to receive prompt reimbursement for all reasonable business expenses incurred by him on behalf of the Company in accordance with the Company&#x2019;s policies and procedures in effect from time to time.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Benefits.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	During the Employment Term, the Executive shall be entitled to participate in or receive benefits under any life or disability insurance, health, pension, retirement, accident, and other employee benefit plans, programs and arrangements made generally available by the Company to its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	senior
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	executive
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	officers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, subject to and on a basis consistent with the terms, conditions and overall administration of such plans and arrangements in effect from time to time. In accordance with the Company&#x2019;s policies in effect from time to time applicable to the Executive, the Executive shall also be entitled to paid vacation in any fiscal year during the Employment Term as well as all paid holidays given by the Company to its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	senior executive officers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(e)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Automobile.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	During the Employment Term, the Executive shall receive an automobile allowance (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Automobile Allowance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of $1,100 per month less applicable taxes, payable in accordance with Company policy, but in no event later than March 15th of the year following the year in which the Automobile Allowance will accrue.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(f)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Equity Awards.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	During the Employment Term, the Executive shall be eligible to participate in the Company&#x2019;s equity incentive plan as determined by the Compensation Committee in its sole discretion. The grant timing, form and amount of the equity awards
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Equity Awards
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	shall be determined by the Compensation Committee in its sole discretion. The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	E
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	quity
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	wards shall be granted pursuant to and subject to the terms of the Company&#x2019;s Long-Term Incentive Plan (or any successor plan) and an award agreement to be entered into between the Company and the Executive.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	4.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Termination and Compensation Thereon
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Termination.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, the Executive&#x2019;s employment pursuant to this Agreement may be terminated either by the Executive or the Company at any time and for any reason. The term &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Termination Date
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D; shall mean the date
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	upon which the Executive&#x2019;s employment is terminated (i) by his death, (ii) by his Incapacity (as defined in Section 4(c)), (iii) otherwise in accordance with this Agreement, or (iv) for any other reason, the Executive incurs a Separation from Service (as defined in Section 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(c)).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Death
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Executive&#x2019;s employment shall terminate upon his death.&nbsp;&nbsp;In such event, the Company shall, within thirty (30) days following the date of death, pay to such person as the Executive shall have designated in a notice filed with the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Person
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, or, if no such
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	P
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	erson shall have been designated, to the Executive&#x2019;s estate,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	a lump-sum amount equal to the sum of (A) a prorated portion of 75% of the Executive&#x2019;s then current Salary, with the prorated amount to be determined based on the number of days that the Executive was employed by the Company in the year during which the Termination Date occurs, (B) the Executive&#x2019;s Salary for the remainder of the Employment Term, (C) the maximum annual contribution under the Company&#x2019;s deferred compensation plan of seven and a half percent (7.5%) of the Executive&#x2019;s total base salary and annual cash bonus (with such maximum amount to be determined in accordance with the terms of the applicable deferred compensation plan) that would have been made during the remainder of the Employment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Term
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and (D) two (2) times the Executive&#x2019;s Target Bonus, in the case of each of clauses (B), (C) and (D) at the rates in effect as of the Termination Date (the lump sum amount determined in accordance with this Section 4(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Termination Amount
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(ii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Upon Executive's death, the Company shall, within thirty (30) days following the date of death, also pay to such Person as Executive shall have designated in a notice filed with the Company, or if no such Person shall have been designated, to his estate, a lump-sum amount equal to (A) any accrued and unpaid Salary, Automobile Allowance, vacation time and benefits through the date of death, and (B) any earned but unpaid bonuses payable to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Executive as determined by the Compensation Committee for any fiscal periods of the Company ending prior to the date of death.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(iii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In addition, upon Executive&#x2019;s death, any Equity Awards granted to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Executive that would not vest on or prior to the Termination Date shall vest and, if applicable, be exercisable immediately and, notwithstanding any termination of employment provisions set forth in the applicable agreement or related plan, such Equity Awards shall continue to be exercisable until their original stated expiration date.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Incapacity
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	If, in the reasonable judgment of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Compensation Committee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, as a result of the Executive&#x2019;s incapacity due to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	a medically determinable physical or mental illness, the Executive shall have been absent from his full-time duties as described hereunder for the entire period of twelve
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(12) consecutive months
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	(&#x201C;Incapacity&#x201D;),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the Executive&#x2019;s employment shall terminate at the end of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	twelve
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	12)-month period as provided in this Section 4(c). In such event
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the Company shall give prompt notice to Executive of any such termination;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(ii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the Company shall pay
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to the Executive a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	lump-sum amount equal to the Termination Amount
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
